<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
<div class="hero-bg"></div>
<div class="hero-content">
<div class="badge">ABOUT US</div>
<h1>How MTP Group Fulfillment Works</h1>
<p class="hero-sub">From a small warehouse in 2015 to processing 60,000+ shipments per month &mdash; our story of building Ukraine's most resilient fulfillment infrastructure.</p>
</div>
</section>

<!-- OUR STORY -->
<section class="story"><div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">OUR STORY</div>
<h2 class="sec-h2">A decade of building logistics that work</h2>
<div class="story-grid">
<div class="story-text">
<p>MTP Group Fulfillment was founded in 2015 by Mykola Liashchuk with a straightforward idea: Ukrainian e-commerce businesses deserve warehouse logistics that are fast, transparent, and built for scale. What started as a single 200-square-meter storage space in the Kyiv region with a team of just three people has grown into one of Ukraine's most recognized 3PL fulfillment operations.</p>
<p>Over the next ten years, the company grew from handling a handful of parcels per day to processing thousands of orders every morning before lunch. The team expanded from the original 3 to more than 50 full-time employees — warehouse operators, account managers, IT specialists, and quality control staff. Each person was hired not just for skill, but for the ability to stay calm under pressure, because the true test of a logistics company is not how it performs on a normal Tuesday, but how it performs when everything goes sideways.</p>
<p>By 2020, demand had outgrown the original facility. Mykola made the decision to open a second warehouse rather than simply expanding the first — a strategic choice driven by the principle of geographic diversification. When the full-scale invasion began in February 2022, that decision proved prescient. Both facilities remained operational, and MTP Group did not miss a single day of shipping. Not one.</p>
</div>
<div >
<div class="story-highlight">
<p><strong>2015</strong> &mdash; Founded. First warehouse, team of 3, serving 5 clients.</p>
<p><strong>2018</strong> &mdash; Reached 50 active clients. Implemented custom WMS with address storage.</p>
<p><strong>2020</strong> &mdash; Opened second warehouse in Bilohorodka for geographic diversification.</p>
<p><strong>2022</strong> &mdash; Installed 3 generators, Starlink, dual fiber. Zero downtime during invasion.</p>
<p><strong>2024</strong> &mdash; 150+ clients. Entered Top-50 Nova Poshta shippers by volume.</p>
<p><strong>2025</strong> &mdash; Processing 60,000+ shipments per month. Team of 50+ specialists.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></section>

<!-- WAREHOUSES -->
<section class="warehouses"><div class="ctr">
<div class="badge">INFRASTRUCTURE</div>
<h2 class="sec-h2">Two warehouses, one mission</h2>
<p class="sec-sub" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.5)">Geographic diversification is not a luxury — it is a core operational requirement for any logistics company operating in a country at war. Our two-site model ensures that even if one facility faces disruption, the other absorbs the load with zero delay.</p>
<div class="wh-grid">
<div class="wh-card">
<div class="wh-label">Main facility</div>
<h3>Shchaslyve — 2,800 m²</h3>
<p>Located minutes from Boryspil International Airport (KBP) — Ukraine's busiest air cargo hub. This is our primary fulfillment center where the majority of daily order processing takes place. The proximity to the airport means inbound air freight inventory moves from the tarmac to our shelves within hours, not days.</p>
<p>The facility houses our central WMS servers, main packing stations, and the primary Nova Poshta pickup point with multiple daily collections.</p>
<div style="margin-top:16px">
<span class="wh-tag">Address storage</span>
<span class="wh-tag">WMS</span>
<span class="wh-tag">3 generators</span>
<span class="wh-tag">Starlink</span>
<span class="wh-tag">Dual fiber</span>
<span class="wh-tag">Airport proximity</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class="wh-card">
<div class="wh-label">Backup facility</div>
<h3>Bilohorodka — 1,100 m²</h3>
<p>Situated on the western edge of the Kyiv region, Bilohorodka (1,100 m²) provides geographic diversification and additional capacity. When peak season hits — Black Friday, pre-holiday rushes, or flash sales — this facility absorbs the surge without impacting assembly speed at the main site.</p>
<p>The Bilohorodka warehouse also serves as a dedicated hub for heavy and oversized goods, with reinforced pallet racking and forklift access designed for items weighing 30 to 60 kg per unit.</p>
<div style="margin-top:16px">
<span class="wh-tag">Overflow capacity</span>
<span class="wh-tag">Heavy goods</span>
<span class="wh-tag">Pallet storage</span>
<span class="wh-tag">Forklift access</span>
<span class="wh-tag">Western Kyiv region</span>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div></section>

<!-- TECHNOLOGY -->
<section class="tech"><div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">TECHNOLOGY</div>
<h2 class="sec-h2">Technology stack behind every shipment</h2>
<div class="tech-grid">
<div class="tech-card"><div class="tech-icon">&#128187;</div><h3>Custom WMS</h3><p>Proprietary warehouse management system with address-based cell storage, real-time inventory tracking, and automated pick-list generation.</p></div>
<div class="tech-card"><div class="tech-icon">&#9201;</div><h3>30-second assembly</h3><p>Average time from order received to parcel packed and labeled. Address storage eliminates walking time — every item has a precise location.</p></div>
<div class="tech-card"><div class="tech-icon">&#128268;</div><h3>API integrations</h3><p>Native connections with Rozetka, Prom.ua, KeyCRM, SalesDrive, WooCommerce, Shopify, OpenCart, and Horoshop. Custom API in 1-3 days.</p></div>
<div class="tech-card"><div class="tech-icon">&#128202;</div><h3>Client dashboard</h3><p>24/7 access to inventory levels, shipment statuses, return tracking, and financial reports. Available on desktop and mobile, fully in English.</p></div>
</div>
</div></section>

<!-- BLACKOUT RESILIENCE -->
<section class="blackout"><div class="ctr">
<div class="badge">RESILIENCE</div>
<h2 class="sec-h2">Blackout-proof by design</h2>
<p class="sec-sub" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.5)">Since February 2022, Ukraine's energy infrastructure has faced unprecedented challenges. We invested early and aggressively to ensure our clients never experience a single minute of fulfillment downtime — regardless of what happens to the national grid.</p>
<div class="bl-grid">
<div class="bl-card"><div class="bl-icon">&#9889;</div><h3>3 industrial generators</h3><p>Diesel generators with automatic switchover provide uninterrupted power to warehouse operations, WMS servers, barcode scanners, and packing stations. Fuel reserves maintained for 72+ hours of autonomous operation.</p></div>
<div class="bl-card"><div class="bl-icon">&#127760;</div><h3>2 fiber + Starlink</h3><p>Two independent fiber-optic internet providers ensure connectivity for WMS and carrier API communication. Starlink satellite terminal serves as a tertiary fallback — the last line of defense that has never needed to be the only line.</p></div>
<div class="bl-card"><div class="bl-icon">&#128170;</div><h3>Zero downtime since 2022</h3><p>Through rolling blackouts, targeted strikes, and severe winter energy deficits, MTP Group has maintained uninterrupted fulfillment operations. Every order was picked, packed, and shipped on schedule. Every single day.</p></div>
</div>
<div style="text-align:center;margin-top:12px"><span class="bl-badge">&#10003; OPERATIONAL CONTINUITY VERIFIED</span></div>
</div></section>

<!-- KEY NUMBERS -->
<section class="numbers"><div class="ctr">
<div class="badge badge-dark">KEY NUMBERS</div>
<h2 class="sec-h2">MTP Group in figures</h2>
<div class="num-grid">
<div class="num-cell"><div class="num-val">10</div><div class="num-label">years in<br>business</div></div>
<div class="num-cell"><div class="num-val">6,000</div><div class="num-label">orders/day<br>capacity</div></div>
<div class="num-cell"><div class="num-val">30 sec</div><div class="num-label">order<br>assembly</div></div>
<div class="num-cell"><div class="num-val">150+</div><div class="num-label">active<br>clients</div></div>
<div class="num-cell"><div class="num-val">Top 50</div><div class="num-label">Nova Poshta<br>shipper</div></div>
</div>
</div></section>

<!-- SEO ARTICLE -->
<section class="seo-article"><div class="ctr">
<h2>Why Choose a Fulfillment Partner in Kyiv Region</h2>

<h3>The strategic advantage of Kyiv-based logistics</h3>
<p>When international e-commerce brands consider entering the Ukrainian market or optimizing their domestic fulfillment, the first question is always about location. And the answer, for most product categories and delivery profiles, points firmly to the Kyiv region. Ukraine's capital and its surrounding oblast account for roughly 30 percent of all e-commerce order volume in the country. A warehouse positioned here means shorter average delivery times to the largest concentration of buyers, lower last-mile shipping costs, and access to the densest network of carrier pickup points.</p>

<h3>Proximity to Boryspil Airport: not just convenient, but critical</h3>
<p>For brands shipping inventory to Ukraine from abroad, the location of the fulfillment warehouse relative to the primary air cargo hub matters enormously. Boryspil International Airport handles the vast majority of international air freight entering the country. A fulfillment center located within a short drive of the airport means inbound goods can be received, inspected, barcoded, and placed into addressed warehouse cells on the same day they clear customs.</p>

<h3>Geographic diversification: a lesson learned the hard way</h3>
<p>The events of 2022 taught every logistics operator in Ukraine an unforgettable lesson: redundancy is not optional. Companies that relied on a single warehouse location, regardless of how modern or well-equipped it was, discovered that geographic concentration is a single point of failure. MTP Group's two-warehouse model — with facilities in Shchaslive (2,800 m²) and Bilohorodka (1,100 m²), positioned on opposite sides of the Kyiv agglomeration — was designed specifically to mitigate this risk.</p>

<h3>What to look for in a Kyiv-region fulfillment partner</h3>
<p>Not every warehouse near Kyiv is created equal. When evaluating potential fulfillment partners, international clients should prioritize several factors beyond basic pricing. First, verify the power backup infrastructure. Second, ask about internet redundancy. Third, examine the technology stack. Fourth, investigate carrier relationships. Fifth, request client references in your product category.</p>

<h3>The bottom line</h3>
<p>Choosing a fulfillment partner in the Kyiv region is not just about proximity to customers — although that alone justifies the decision for most brands. It is about access to air cargo infrastructure, carrier network density, a proven approach to operational resilience, and a technology-forward logistics ecosystem that has been pressure-tested under conditions no other European market has had to face.</p>
</div></section>

</Base>

<style is:global>
:root{--black:#000;--white:#fff;--red:#e63329;--gray:#f5f5f5;--muted:#666;--fd:'DM Serif Display',serif;--fb:'DM Sans',sans-serif}
.ctr{max-width:1200px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px}
.badge{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.25);border-radius:100px;padding:8px 20px;font-size:11px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:3px;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(255,255,255,.7);margin-bottom:24px}
.badge::before{content:'';width:6px;height:6px;background:var(--red);border-radius:50%}
.badge-dark{border-color:rgba(0,0,0,.15);color:var(--muted)}

.hero{position:relative;min-height:90vh;background:#000;color:#fff;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;padding:120px 0 80px;overflow:hidden}
.hero-bg{position:absolute;inset:0;background:url('/images/tild3262-6663-4666-b965-333937343739__img_4849.jpg') center/cover;opacity:.18}
.hero-content{position:relative;z-index:2;padding:0 8vw;max-width:800px}
.hero h1{font-family:var(--fd,'DM Serif Display',serif);font-size:clamp(36px,5.5vw,64px);font-weight:400;line-height:1;margin-bottom:28px}
.hero-sub{font-size:clamp(16px,1.8vw,20px);color:rgba(255,255,255,.6);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:0}
.sec-h2{font-family:var(--fd,'DM Serif Display',serif);font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,48px);font-weight:400;margin-bottom:48px}
.sec-sub{font-size:16px;color:var(--muted,#666);line-height:1.7;max-width:680px;margin-bottom:48px}
.story{padding:100px 0;background:#fff}
.story-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:64px;align-items:center}
.story-text p{font-size:15px;line-height:1.8;color:#444;margin-bottom:16px}
.story-highlight{background:var(--gray,#f5f5f5);border-left:4px solid var(--red,#e63329);padding:24px 28px;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;margin-top:24px}
.story-highlight p{font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;color:#555;margin:0}
.warehouses{padding:100px 0;background:#0a0a0a;color:#fff}
.wh-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:40px}
.wh-card{background:rgba(255,255,255,.04);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);border-radius:8px;padding:40px;transition:border-color .3s}.wh-card:hover{border-color:rgba(255,255,255,.2)}
.wh-label{font-size:11px;letter-spacing:3px;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--red,#e63329);margin-bottom:12px;font-weight:500}
.wh-card h3{font-family:var(--fd,'DM Serif Display',serif);font-size:24px;font-weight:400;margin-bottom:16px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.95)}
.wh-card p{font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);margin-bottom:8px}
.wh-tag{display:inline-block;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);border-radius:100px;padding:4px 14px;font-size:11px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.5);margin:4px 4px 0 0}
.tech{padding:100px 0;background:#fff}
.tech-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:1px;background:#e0e0e0;border:1px solid #e0e0e0;border-radius:4px;overflow:hidden}
.tech-card{background:#fff;padding:36px 28px;transition:background .3s}.tech-card:hover{background:var(--gray,#f5f5f5)}
.tech-icon{font-size:32px;margin-bottom:14px}
.tech-card h3{font-size:16px;font-weight:500;margin-bottom:8px}.tech-card p{font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;color:var(--muted,#666)}
.blackout{padding:100px 0;background:#111;color:#fff}
.bl-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:32px}
.bl-card{text-align:center;padding:40px 24px}
.bl-icon{font-size:40px;margin-bottom:16px}
.bl-card h3{font-size:18px;font-weight:500;margin-bottom:8px;color:rgba(255,255,255,.9)}.bl-card p{font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(255,255,255,.5)}
.bl-badge{display:inline-block;background:rgba(34,197,94,.12);color:#22c55e;font-size:12px;font-weight:500;padding:6px 16px;border-radius:100px;margin-top:48px;letter-spacing:1px}
.numbers{padding:100px 0;background:var(--gray,#f5f5f5)}
.num-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:0;border-top:1px solid #ddd;border-left:1px solid #ddd}
.num-cell{padding:40px 24px;text-align:center;border-right:1px solid #ddd;border-bottom:1px solid #ddd}
.num-val{font-family:var(--fd,'DM Serif Display',serif);font-size:clamp(28px,3.5vw,44px);font-weight:400;color:var(--red,#e63329);margin-bottom:8px}
.num-label{font-size:12px;color:var(--muted,#666);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;line-height:1.5}
.seo-article{padding:100px 0}
.seo-article h2{font-family:var(--fd,'DM Serif Display',serif);font-size:clamp(28px,3.5vw,42px);font-weight:400;margin-bottom:40px}
.seo-article h3{font-size:20px;font-weight:500;margin:32px 0 12px}
.seo-article p{font-size:15px;color:#444;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px;max-width:780px}
@media(max-width:768px){
.hero{min-height:auto;padding:100px 0 60px}.hero-content{padding:0 24px}
.hero h1{font-size:clamp(32px,8vw,48px)}
.story-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:40px}
.wh-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
.tech-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}
.bl-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}
.num-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}.num-cell:last-child{grid-column:span 2}
.final-form{flex-direction:column}
}

.svc-card,.service-card,.num-card,.adv-card,.ben-card,.wh-card,.case-stats,.step{opacity:1!important;transform:none!important}
</style>

<script is:inline>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function(){
var obs=new IntersectionObserver(function(en){en.forEach(function(e){if(e.isIntersecting){e.target.classList.add('visible');obs.unobserve(e.target);}});},{threshold:.15});
document.querySelectorAll('.reveal').forEach(function(el,i){el.style.transitionDelay=(i%3)*.1+'s';obs.observe(el);});

function applyPhoneMask(inp){
inp.addEventListener('input',function(){var v=this.value.replace(/\D/g,'');if(v.startsWith('380'))v=v.slice(2);else if(v.startsWith('38'))v=v.slice(2);else if(v.startsWith('80'))v='0'+v.slice(2);var m='+38 (';if(v.length>0)m+=v.substring(0,3);if(v.length>=3)m+=') ';if(v.length>3)m+=v.substring(3,6);if(v.length>=6)m+=' ';if(v.length>6)m+=v.substring(6,8);if(v.length>=8)m+=' ';if(v.length>8)m+=v.substring(8,10);this.value=m;});
inp.addEventListener('focus',function(){if(!this.value)this.value='+38 (';});
inp.addEventListener('blur',function(){if(this.value==='+38 (')this.value='';});
}
document.querySelectorAll('input[type="tel"]').forEach(applyPhoneMask);

function handleForm(form){
form.addEventListener('submit',function(e){e.preventDefault();var ph=form.querySelector('input[name="phone"]').value;var clean=ph.replace(/\D/g,'');if(clean.length<12){form.querySelector('input[name="phone"]').style.borderColor='#e63329';return;}
var leads=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('mtp_crm_leads')||'[]');leads.push({id:Date.now(),company:'Inquiry from About EN',contact:'',phone:ph,email:'',shipments:0,type:'other',source:'About page EN',status:'new',date:new Date().toISOString().split('T')[0],comments:[{text:'Form on About EN page',date:new Date().toLocaleString('uk-UA')}],onboarding:[false,false,false,false,false,false,false]});localStorage.setItem('mtp_crm_leads',JSON.stringify(leads));
fetch('/api/telegram',{method:'POST',headers:{'Content-Type':'application/json'},body:JSON.stringify({phone:ph,page:location.pathname})}).catch(function(){});
form.innerHTML='<div style="text-align:center;padding:20px"><p style="color:#22c55e;font-size:18px;font-weight:500">\u2705 Thank you!</p><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);font-size:14px;margin-top:8px">We will call you back shortly</p></div>';
setTimeout(function(){window.location.href='/en/thanks/';},1500);});
}
var ff=document.getElementById('finalForm');if(ff)handleForm(ff);
});
</script>
